title: WSDG November Technical Presentation
description:
Python in Excel
by Paul Doolittle

Abstract:
Excel has been the world's most widely used analysis tool for decades. Python has been the language of choice for data science, automation, and AI. Now, they live together in the same workbook.

This talk will explore the power of **Python in Excel** \- what it is\, and how it changes the game for analysts\, developers\, and decision\-makers\. We'll look at practical use cases\, from wrangling data with pandas to building models that go far beyond traditional formulas\. You'll see live examples of how Python complements Excel rather than replacing it\, bridging the gap between quick spreadsheet tsks and full\-scale programming\.

Whether you're an Excel power user curious about Python or a Pythonista curious about Excel, you'll leave with a roadmap to get started and a sense of the **data-shaped future of software development**.

Bio:
Paul is a retired pharmacist, former business owner, and lifelong learner who has pivoted into the software/data-analytics space. He started in Android development but now focuses on **Excel, Python, and data analysis**, framing his work as "dispensing data" rather than prescriptions. With a beginning practice in data consulting under the banner *Data Compounded, LLC*, Paul is passionate about teaching others how to combine familiar tools like Excel with modern programming and AI. Off ours, he's a first-time grandfather who trains consistently - protein, resistance training and Zone 2 cardio. He and his Ukrainian wife have opened their home to Ukrainian refugees.
\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
This hybrid meeting will be available both in-person and remotely. For those attending in person, we will be at the Williamsburg Regional Library, Conference Room B.

title: üßú‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è The AI Collective HR ‚Ä¢ Vibecoding 101: Launch your idea today
description:
***Are you ready? We're going to design, develop, launch, and understand your idea today.***

**This is a hands-on workshop led by [Ted Patterson](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tedjpatterson/), [Emanuel Perez](https://www.linkedin.com/in/emanuelperez8/), & [Lionel Sapp](https://www.linkedin.com/in/lionelthebldr/)**

This is a hands-on, beginner-friendly workshop where you‚Äôll take your ideas from concept to prototype ‚Äî all in one evening. We‚Äôll guide you step-by-step through researching your website or app idea using **Mobbin**, building your first working prototype using **Bolt and Supabase,** and deploying it live so you can start testing right away with **Microsoft Clarity.**

**What to expect**

* A quick intro to **Vibecoding** ‚Äî how AI can accelerate your creative process
* Guided walkthroughs led by **Ted Patterson**, **Emanuel Perez, and Lionel Sapp**
* Hands-on building with **Mobbin (for website & app patterns)**, **Bolt** (for rapid development), **Supabase** (for database, auth, and APIs), and Microsoft Clarity (for understanding your users)
* Real-time help from mentors and community members
* End the night with your **own live prototype** ready to share and test

\- \- \-

**FAQs**

**What is Vibecoding?**
It‚Äôs a new way to build software using natural language, AI, and no-code tools. You describe what you want ‚Äî the tools help make it real. No traditional coding required.
**Do I need to know how to code?**
No experience needed! If you can describe what you want to build, you‚Äôre ready.
**What should I bring?**
Bring a laptop. We‚Äôll provide Wi-Fi, outlets, and snacks.
**Is this for beginners?**
Yes! Whether it‚Äôs your first project or your tenth, you‚Äôll walk away with something new ‚Äî and running.
**Is this free?**
Yes, but space is limited. Be sure to RSVP early.
**Is parking available?**
Yes. Town Center has five garages with more than 4,380 spaces and 86 on-street spaces available for public use.
Get more info ‚Üí https://pw.virginiabeach.gov/city-property/parking/town-center-parking

title: üßú‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è The AI Collective HR ‚Ä¢ AI, Medicine, and Me
description:
**Medical knowledge now doubles every 73 days, creating a gap doctors can't bridge alone. What if you could use new AI tools to help find the answers?**

Are you, or a loved one, navigating a complex health journey? The old model of "doctor's orders" is being replaced by a new "patient as partner" model‚Äîand AI is the tool that makes it possible.

Join technologist Andrew Stafford and EVMS physician-researcher Atiq Bhatti, MD, for a groundbreaking 60-minute talk.

**What you'll learn**

* How to safely use tools like ChatGPT and Gemini for your own health research.
* The "trust barrier" that keeps doctors from using AI‚Äîand how it's being solved.
* A look at the new, doctor-specific AI tools like **Open Evidence** and **UpToDate Expert AI** that are changing medicine right now.
* How patients, nurses, and small practice owners‚Äînot just giant hospitals‚Äîare at the center of this revolution.

This talk is for empowered patients, healthcare staff (NPs/nurses), small practice owners, and anyone curious about the future of medicine.

* **Networking Opportunities:** Build lasting professional relationships with fellow information security, risk management, and privacy experts.

* **Career Advancement:** Connect with peers and explore career information, mentorship, and employment opportunities.

title: Get on the Bus! The Azure Service Bus with Matthew Hess
description:
Azure Service Bus is Microsoft‚Äôs cloud offering for developing queue and message-based applications. We‚Äôll explore core Azure Service Bus techniques and concepts, including:

* Sending and Receiving messages
* Using Peek-Locks and other receive modes
* Abandoning and Dead Lettering Messages
* Using Topics and Subscriptions
* Processing multiple Messages and Scaling

We‚Äôll also discuss the purpose of message-based architectures and how these technologies can be used to build truly decoupled and reliable microservices.

title: Hampton Roads DevFest 2026
description:
Mark your calendar for Hampton Roads DevFest 2026! This unique gathering will once again spotlight local speakers, showcasing our community's deep and diverse talent.

Hampton Roads DevFest is more than a conference; it's a tribute to our dynamic local developer community. It's an ideal platform to highlight the exceptional places to work in the Hampton Roads area, emphasizing innovative technological strides. This event caters to everyone in the tech sphere, from seasoned developers and industry veterans to emerging talents and students.

Organized by RevolutionVA, a dedicated 501(c)(3) non-profit, our mission is to advance software development education throughout Virginia. Our passion for promoting learning and growth in technology is at the heart of DevFest.

Take advantage of this unparalleled opportunity to network, learn from top industry professionals, and celebrate the remarkable achievements of our tech community. Whether you're looking to sharpen your skills, explore new career pathways, or simply immerse yourself in a community of like-minded tech enthusiasts, Hampton Roads DevFest is your destination.

Join us as we recognize and nurture the extraordinary tech talent that thrives in Hampton Roads. Let's connect, discover, and grow together at Hampton Roads DevFest 2026!
